@startuml
!include ../style.puml

participant Client
participant "RocksDB Iterator" as Iter

note over Iter
  **Sorted Keys in DB**
  1. Account1\\x00<InvTs:110> -> "$200"
  2. Account1\\x00<InvTs:90>  -> "$150"
  3. Account1\\x00<InvTs:50>  -> "$100"
  <color:gray>4. Account2\\x00<InvTs:120> -> "$500"</color>
end note

Client -> Iter: seek("Account1\\x00" + Inverted(100))
note right of Iter
  Iterator jumps to the first key 
  that is >= the seek target.
  
  Target = Account1\\x00<InvTs:100>
  
  Key 1 (InvTs:110) < Target (skip)
  Key 2 (InvTs:90) >= Target! (land here)
end note

Iter --> Client: Iter.value() = "$150"
@enduml
